{"tid":1540011,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"利物浦洗板大行動 DAY 2","createTime":"2019-09-04T10:41:49.000Z","updateTime":"2019-09-04T12:07:17.000Z","uid":160887,"like":7,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":7,"replies":[{"pid":"d98bfcdf4094ec4575208ba986c1c5837d100ddc","tid":1540011,"uid":160887,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-04T10:41:49.000Z","msg":"Liverpool FC 官方仲未肯回應香港球迷會<br />\n行動對準佢地FACEBOOK, TWITTER, INSTAGRAM<br />\n<br />\nWe, Hong Kong Liverpool fans, received an objection email from Liverpool FC requesting the HKSAR official page to delete their statement which criticises the Hong Kong Police. <br />\n<br />\nAs one of the most popular football clubs, we have a responsibility to pursue justice throughout history and today - just as with the Hillsborough Disaster. We share this vision of justice all over the world, thus the abhorrent behaviour of the police must be acknowledged. Recently, Hong Kong police shot innocent protesters and civilians in Hong Kong, many of them are students and teenagers, and the police are now even shooting at journalists. We are just seeking freedom and justice for our next generation, not wanting to be sent to China. <br />\n<br />\nWe know that Liverpool Official may  not wish to engage in any political issues, but it's ultimately about basic human rights... A club with such historical importance should understand what is going on in Hong Kong. We urge that even if our pursuit of justice is not recognised by you, please do not inhibit our efforts to reach our goals. At the very least, we should all honour the meaning of 'You'll Never Walk Alone'. <br />\n<br />\nJustice may come late, but it will always prevail."},{"pid":"ea2961cbede329fc77262fc364f013270c594dac","tid":1540011,"uid":160887,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-04T10:42:38.000Z","msg":"五大訴求 缺一不可"},{"pid":"a30192429e4ef4e9a22dd12a83415c0d7d4dde01","tid":1540011,"uid":160887,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"reply